e%20last%20year%20was%20%243.73%20million%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20an%20island%20realtor%2C%20Fisher%20Real%20Estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacoby%2C%20the%20June%20lawsuit%20alleged%2C%20walked%20across%20his%20property%20at%203%20Tautemo%20Way%20and%20onto%20Belford's%20land.%20On%20his%20own%2C%20he%20used%20a%20chainsaw%20to%20cut%20down%2016%2030-foot-high%20cedar%2C%20cherry%2C%20and%20Leyland%20cypress%20trees%20before%20he%20asked%20his%20landscaper%20to%20help%20him%20clean%20up%20the%20debris%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20and%20an%20attached%20statement%20by%20the%20landscaper%20to%20local%20police%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20loss%20of%20the%20trees%20has%20significantly%20diminished%20the%20value%20and%20character%20of%20the%20Belford%20Property%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20trees%20were%20a%20mature%20and%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20landscape%2C%20planted%20and%20cared%20for%20by%20the%20Belford%20family%20for%20nearly%2050%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacoby's%20home%20was%20recently%20put%20on%20the%20market%20for%20nearly%20%2410%20million%2C%20with%20a%20listing%20that%20boasted%20%26quot%3Bsweeping%20views%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%26quot%3B%20Those%20views%20that%20the%20latest%20listing%20touted%20were%20%26quot%3Bconspicuously%20missing%26quot%3B%20from%20previous%2C%20pre-treegate%20listings%2C%20Belford's%20lawsuit%20said.%20The%20home%20was%20taken%20off%20the%20market%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20usually%20done%20in%20some%20sort%20of%20act%20of%20desperation%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20on%20the%20island%20told%20Business%20Insider%20of%20similar%20illicit%20tree%20trimmings.%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20that%20bump.%20This%20property%20has%20previously%20been%20on%20the%20market%2C%20and%20they%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20sell%20it.%20Therein%20lies%20the%20motivation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cisco%20beach%20nantucket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6882862b85e81483682ea15b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJacoby%20and%20Belford's%20properties%20are%20in%20the%20Cisco%20neighborhood%20of%20Nantucket%2C%20which%20is%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20most%20desirable%20on%20the%20island.%3Cp%3ETim%20Clayton%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJacoby%20is%20facing%20criminal%20charges%20over%20the%20tree-cutting%20ordeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nantucket%20Police%20Department%20has%20charged%20Jacoby%20with%20vandalizing%20property%2C%20a%20felony%2C%20and%20the%20misdemeanors%20of%20trespassing%20and%20cutting%2Fdestroying%20trees%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20police%20confirmed%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20Jacoby%2C%20James%20Merberg%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20criminal%20case%20and%20lawsuit%20but%20said%20that%20Jacoby%20will%20enter%20a%20plea%20of%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20charges.%20Jacoby%20is%20scheduled%20to%20be%20arraigned%20on%20September%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacoby%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20comment%2C%20but%20he%20defended%20his%20actions%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2025%2F07%2F14%2Fmetro%2Fnantucket-dispute-cut-trees-atlantic-ocean-views%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Boston%20Globe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20in%20an%20email%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20trespassing%2C%20I%20was%20clearing%20out%20her%20crappy%20trees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNantucket%2C%20the%20Vineyard%20%E2%80%94%20places%20where%20there%20is%20so%20much%20money%20at%20play%20%E2%80%94%20money%20and%20ego%20can%20get%20in%20the%20way%20very%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Glenn%20Wood%2C%20Belford's%20attorney%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20brazenness%20of%20the%20alleged%20action%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20attention%20it%20has%20gotten%20from%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETree%20law%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20is%20an%20active%20legal%20niche.%20While%20most%20lawsuits%20don't%20accuse%20neighbors%20of%20such%20deliberate%20violations%20and%20most%20payouts%20or%20settlements%20don't%20reach%20seven%20figures%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20number%20of%20high-profile%20disputes%20that%20involve%20stealth%20maneuvers%20and%20big%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f921083b-d1ba-4955-a93c-407d0eac6818%5C%22%3ETree-cutting%20fights%20aren't%20rare%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20trees%20can%20spur%20neighborly%20spats.%20A%20dead%20tree%20causes%20an%20eyesore%3B%20a%20large%20one%20blocks%20a%20view%3B%20a%20tree%20struck%20by%20lightning%20can%20leave%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20look%20at%20the%20subreddit%20%26quot%3Btree%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20150%2C000%20members%2C%20and%20the%20subject%20matter's%20universality%20becomes%20clear.%20Some%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Ftreelaw%2Fcomments%2F1m6i7tp%2Fneighbor_refuses_to_cut_their_willow_that_is%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20asking%20for%20advice%2C%20like%20what%20to%20do%20about%20a%20neighbor's%20willow%20whose%20branches%20bow%20onto%20their%20roof.%20Others%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Ftreelaw%2Fcomments%2F1m1eobe%2Fnew_missouri_law_bans_6_invasive_plants_for_sale%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20latest%20news%20in%20the%20space%2C%20like%20a%20Missouri%20law%20regarding%20the%20sale%20of%20invasive%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Hampshire-based%20attorney%20Israel%20Piedra%2C%20who%20started%20the%20website%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FNewEnglandTreeLaw.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewEnglandTreeLaw.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20tree-cutting%20disputes%20are%20%26quot%3Bmore%20common%20than%20people%20would%20think.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPiedra%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20firm%20Welts%2C%20White%20%26amp%3B%20Fontaine%2C%20P.C.%2C%20said%20he%20has%20carved%20out%20a%20practice%20representing%20property%20owners%20who%20have%20had%20their%20trees%20cut%20down%20without%20permission%20and%20has%20handled%20more%20than%20100%20such%20cases%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20primarily%20out%20of%20New%20Hampshire%20and%20Massachusetts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20cases%2C%20he%20said%2C%20do%20not%20involve%20accusations%20as%20%26quot%3Begregious%26quot%3B%20as%20those%20in%20the%20Nantucket%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20commonly%2C%20you're%20dealing%20with%20a%20case%20where%20there%20isn't%20actually%20intentional%20conduct%2C%20or%20there%20isn't%20malicious%20intent%2C%26quot%3B%20Piedra%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20cases%20he%20has%20handled%20involve%20a%20careless%20homeowner%20who%20did%20not%20check%20the%20property%20line%20before%20cutting%20down%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20try%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%20a%20mistake%2C%20or%20at%20least%20maintain%20some%20level%20of%20plausible%20deniability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20these%20cases%20are%20usually%20settled%20out%20of%20court%20through%20a%20neighbor's%20homeowner's%20insurance%20or%20a%20contractor's%20commercial%20liability%20insurance%2C%20and%20don't%20involve%20such%20high-value%20property%20or%20high-value%20damage%20claims.%20Piedra%20said%20he%20has%20never%20had%20a%20case%20settle%20for%20more%20than%20%241%20million%2C%20though%20some%20cases%20have%20settled%20for%20six-figure%20sums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETimber%20trespass%20laws%2C%20Piedra%20said%2C%20vary%20state%20by%20state%2C%20with%20the%20New%20England%20states%20of%20Maine%2C%20Vermont%2C%20and%20Massachusetts%20having%20some%20of%20the%20strongest%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20looking%20for%20lawyers%20that%20do%20this%20kind%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d737362-c65a-4514-bc64-4ac7fe2d8ea4%5C%22%3EWhen%20money%20grows%20on%20trees%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20allegations%20in%20the%20Nantucket%20lawsuit%20are%20extreme%20%E2%80%94%20crossing%20a%20property%20line%2C%20taking%20down%20healthy%20trees%2C%20the%20expenses%20involved.%20Putting%20in%20replacement%20trees%2C%20which%20would%20have%20to%20be%20brought%20from%20off%20the%20island%2C%20would%20cost%20nearly%20%24500%2C000%2C%20Belford's%20lawsuit%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20other%20high-profile%2C%20big-ticket%20squabbles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20incident%20on%20Nantucket's%20sister%20island%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarthas-vineyard-is-more-than-just-a-posh-vacationland-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMartha's%20Vineyard%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ended%20in%202023%20with%20a%20%242.5%20million%20settlement%20after%20inn%20owners%20were%20accused%20of%20having%20more%20than%20100%20trees%20cut%20down%20on%20a%20neighboring%20property%20in%20a%20move%20that%2C%20a%20lawsuit%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwreaked%20havoc%20and%20devastation%20akin%20to%20a%20war%20zone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202006%20case%2C%20a%20defendant%20in%20Vermont%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%20%241.8%20million%20in%20damages%20after%20timber%20trespassing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20most%20publicized%20instances%20of%20human-on-tree%20destruction%2C%20last%20year%2C%20Amelia%20and%20Arthur%20Bond%20agreed%20to%20pay%20more%20than%20%241.7%20million%20in%20fines%20and%20settlements%20after%20they'd%20applied%20herbicide%20to%20the%20area%20near%20the%20oak%20trees%20on%20the%20property%20of%20Lisa%20Gorman%2C%20the%20widow%20of%20the%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-family-behind-the-ll-bean-empire-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EL.L.%20Bean%3C%2Fa%3E%20president%20and%20heir%2C%20in%20the%20idyllic%20New%20England%20coastal%20town%20