0Sitaphal%20(Custard%20Apple).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENMK-01%20(Golden)%20is%20cultivated%20in%2016%20Indian%20states%20and%20even%20in%20Tanzania%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F458835%2Fcsir-neeri-eco-rejuvenation-technology-vidarbha-maharashtra-scientist-insights%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20in%20dryland%20zones.%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20drought-prone%20districts%20like%20Solapur%2C%20Beed%2C%20Aurangabad%2C%20and%20Parbhani%2C%20has%20seen%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20this%20variety%E2%80%94followed%20by%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F389465%2Fparmeshwar-thorat-avocado-organic-farming-drought-beed-maharashtra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFarmers%20also%20praise%20its%20high%20yields%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20go%20up%20to%2010%20tonnes%20per%20acre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBut%20who%20developed%20the%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20sat%20down%20with%2067-year-old%20farmer%20innovator%20Navnath%20Kaspate%2C%20the%20mind%20behind%20this%20unique%20variety.%20In%202019%2C%20his%20innovation%20earned%20him%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20from%20the%20Protection%20of%20Plant%20Varieties%20and%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(PPV%26amp%3BRA).%20Today%2C%20he%20owns%20a%2070-acre%20farm%E2%80%94Madhuban%20Farm%20and%20Nursery%E2%80%94which%20is%20home%20to%2042%20different%20varieties%20of%20custard%20apples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETracing%20the%20history%20of%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelonging%20to%20the%20Annonaceae%20family%2C%20custard%20apple%E2%80%94heart-shaped%2C%20spherical%2C%20or%20irregular%E2%80%94features%20quilted%20skin%20that%20turns%20brown%20as%20it%20ripens.%20Originally%20from%20South%20America%20and%20the%20West%20Indies%2C%20Sitaphal%20was%20introduced%20to%20India%20by%20the%20Portuguese%20in%20the%2016th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20depictions%20of%20custard%20apples%20appear%20in%20ancient%20Indian%20sculptures%2C%20such%20as%20those%20at%20Bharhut%2C%20Sanchi%2C%20Ajanta%2C%20and%20Mathura%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20the%202nd%20century%20BCE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20varieties%20like%20Balanagar%2C%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20and%20Lal%20Sitaphal%20exist%2C%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20is%20expanding%20rapidly%20due%20to%20its%20strong%20market%20acceptance%20and%20profitability%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStarted%20by%20one%20innovator%2C%20many%20followed%20suit%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20dryland%20crop%2C%20custard%20apple%20requires%20minimal%20irrigation%E2%80%94especially%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%E2%80%94and%20is%20well-suited%20for%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20resulting%20in%20fewer%20pest%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-1536x1152.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-150x113.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F