f%20cross-pollination.%20These%20cannot%20be%20found%20elsewhere.%20Only%20when%20one%20registers%20a%20variety%20with%20an%20authority%20like%20the%20PPV%20%26amp%3B%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(FRA)%2C%20can%20it%20be%20officially%20recognised.%20I%20have%20selected%20some%20of%20them%2C%20filed%20for%20patents%2C%20and%20started%20acquiring%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20(IPR).%20In%20India%2C%20living%20things%20like%20plants%20and%20animals%2C%20and%20the%20natural%20processes%20used%20to%20produce%20them%2C%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20patented%E2%80%94but%20they%20can%20receive%20other%20forms%20of%20IPR%20protection%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolapur%E2%80%99s%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra%20highlights%20several%20of%20his%20innovative%20custard%20apple%20varieties%3A%20Annona-2%2C%20NMK-1%2C%20NMK-2%2C%20NMK-3%2C%20and%20Finger%20Prints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%20most%20popular%20varieties%20is%20NMK-1%2C%20which%20he%20began%20developing%20in%202002.%20Farmers%20love%20it%20for%20its%20attractive%20colour%20and%20size%2C%20the%20good%20number%20of%20fruits%20each%20plant%20produces%2C%20and%20its%20uniform%20shape%E2%80%94making%20it%20ideal%20for%20export.%20The%20fruits%20also%20stay%20unripe%20on%20the%20plant%20for%2020%E2%80%9325%20days%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20crack%20after%20harvesting%2C%20and%20suffer%20fewer%20losses%20during%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EComparing%20varieties%3A%20market%20research%2C%20pricing%2C%20yield%2C%20taste%2C%20and%20farmer%20preference%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20leads%20custard%20apple%20production%20in%20India%2C%20with%20other%20popular%20varieties%20like%20Lal%20Sitaphal%2C%20Balanagari%2C%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%20also%20grown%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2055%2C000%20hectares%20of%20custard%20apple%20farms%20in%20India%2C%207%2C000%20hectares%20are%20in%20Maharashtra%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustard%20apples%20are%20traded%20daily%20in%20and%20outside%20the%20state%2C%20with%20supplies%20reaching%20markets%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Pune%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20and%20Delhi.%20From%20market%20yards%20in%20Pune%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%2C%20the%20creamy%2C%20grainy-fleshed%20fruit%20is%20distributed%20to%20fruit%20stalls%20and%20malls%20in%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20Balanagar%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20NMK-01%20yields%20up%20to%2012%20tonnes%20per%20acre%20(versus%20five%20to%20six%20tonnes)%20and%20commands%20a%20higher%20price.%20However%2C%20while%20its%20appearance%20and%20sweetness%20appeal%20to%20many%2C%20some%20growers%20and%20consumers%20find%20its%20flavour%20less%20desirable%20than%20local%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20970px)%20100vw%2C%20970px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22970%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%20970w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476010%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22728%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22